Title: Lord Tilbury
Description: Not a tall man an runs somewhat to fat.  Similar to Napoleon.
Author of The Care of the Pig

Title: Lady Worplesdon
Description: We run to height a bit in our family and there's about five-foot-nine of Aunt Agatha, topped off with a beaky nose, an eagle eye, and a lot of grey hair, and the general effect is pretty formidable.
Resident of a country seat in Shropshire, notable for his scandalous Reminiscences
A very personable looney who kept pet rabbits in his bedroom

Title: Lord Yaxley
Description: Devoted his entire life to the pleasures of the table, and discovered that alcohol was a food well in advance of modern medical thought.
Renowned in the early days for his ability to fall in love with every girl he meets.
Bald and round-headed (the upper portion of his head is compared to the dome of St. Paul's Cathedral) with thick, black eyebrows and (usually) a severe expression of face.

Title: 8th Earl of Sidcup
Description: An amateur fascist dictator, designer of women's underclothing and silver expert
Dislikes being disturbed from his sleep or being scratched under the ears
Can mimic a hen laying an egg
A day boy at Wrykyn and a good fast bowler
Very keen cricket captain at Sedleigh
A wealthy businessman and collector of rare books
An obnoxious child, a popular target for kidnappers
